   abstract  = {Two strongly coupled quantum dots are theoretically and
experimentally investigated. In conductance measurements on a GaAs based
low-dimensional system additional features to the Coulomb blockade have been
detected at low temperatures. These regions of finite conductivity are compared
with theoretical investigations of a strongly coupled quantum dot system and
good agreement between the theoretical and the experimental results has been
found.},
